<subSubSection id="CAAE6535FFC8FFA3FF7BFDDFFB6EFDF5" box="[189,1219,515,590]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFC8FFA3FF7BFDDFFEB0FDA6" blockId="116.[189,285,515,541]" box="[189,285,515,541]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<heading id="D94381D2FFC8FFA3FF7BFDDFFEB0FDA6" bold="true" box="[189,285,515,541]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FF7BFDDFFEB0FDA6" bold="true" box="[189,285,515,541]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFC8FFA3FF7BFDEFFB6EFDF5" blockId="116.[189,1219,563,590]" box="[189,1219,563,590]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
Caves, as well as epigeically in forests of 
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FD6EFDEFFCFCFDF6" box="[680,849,563,589]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Tilia-Fraxinus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FCA6FDE8FB94FDF5" box="[864,1081,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FCA6FDE8FC6FFDF5" box="[864,962,564,590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Quercus</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FC0AFDE8FB94FDF5" baseAuthorityName="David" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[972,1081,564,590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Carpinus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FBB5FDE8FB11FDF6" box="[1139,1212,564,589]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FBB5FDE8FB11FDF6" box="[1139,1212,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Fagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAAE6535FFC8FFA3FF7BFDABFD29FC23" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFC8FFA3FF7BFDABFE82FD2A" blockId="116.[189,303,631,657]" box="[189,303,631,657]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<heading id="D94381D2FFC8FFA3FF7BFDABFE82FD2A" bold="true" box="[189,303,631,657]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FF7BFDABFE82FD2A" bold="true" box="[189,303,631,657]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFC8FFA3FF7BFD7BFCE9FD5C" blockId="116.[189,1398,679,743]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
Males are rare, and parthenogenesis has been suggested for this species, supported by the presence of bacteria of 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FE87FD10FDF4FD5D" authority="Hertig, 1936" authorityName="Hertig" authorityYear="1936" box="[321,601,716,742]" class="Alphaproteobacteria" family="Anaplasmataceae" genus="Wolbachia" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Rickettsiales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FE87FD10FE10FD5D" box="[321,445,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Wolbachia</emphasis>
Hertig, 1936
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFC8FFA3FDAEFD10FC95FD5C" author="Mock A. &amp; Tajovsky K. &amp; Zurovcova M. &amp; Jarosova A. &amp; Kocourek P. &amp; Gruber J. &amp; Angyal D. &amp; Spelda J." box="[616,824,716,743]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="234 - 256" refId="ref37881" refString="Mock A., Tajovsky K., Zurovcova M., Jarosova A., Kocourek P., Gruber J., Angyal D. &amp; Spelda J. 2016. Hungarosoma bokori Verhoeff, 1928 (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida): new insights into its taxonomy, systematics, molecular genetics, biogeography and ecology. Zootaxa 4178 (2): 234 - 256. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4178.2.4" type="journal article" year="2016">
Mock 
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FD70FD11FD5CFD5D" box="[694,753,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFC8FFA3FF7BFCD3FD29FC23" blockId="116.[189,1398,783,921]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
The status of this species, as that of the genus and the family, is uncertain: 
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFC8FFA3FBE9FCD3FABBFC92" author="Antic D. &amp; Rada T. &amp; Makarov S. E." box="[1071,1302,783,809]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="289 - 306" refId="ref33864" refString="Antic D. Z, Rada T. &amp; Makarov S. E. 2018 c. Dalmatosomatidae, a new monotypic family, and Dalmatosoma agaricum gen. et sp. nov. (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida: Craspedosomatidea) from Croatia, Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa 4403 (2): 289 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4403.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">
Antić 
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FBBEFCCCFB19FC92" box="[1144,1204,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">et al.</emphasis>
(2018c)
</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the gonopods of 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FE35FCE9FDC5FCF5" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1928" box="[499,616,820,846]" class="Diplopoda" family="Hungarosomatidae" genus="Hungarosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bokori">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FE35FCE9FDC5FCF5" box="[499,616,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">H. bokori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fully coincide with those of 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FC08FCE8FE29FCC8" authority="(Verhoeff, 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Verhoeff" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Diplopoda" family="Craspedosomatidae" genus="Ochogona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervina" subGenus="Octeicosisoma">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FC08FCE8FBE5FCF5" box="[974,1096,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Ochogona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FB9BFCE8FAA7FCF5" box="[1117,1290,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Octeicosisoma</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFC8FFA3FAD8FCE9FADBFCF5" box="[1310,1398,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">cervina</emphasis>
(Verhoeff, 1899)
</taxonomicName>
, currently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFC8FFA3FDB3FC85FCF2FCC8" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1843" box="[629,863,857,883]" class="Diplopoda" family="Craspedosomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Craspedosomatidae</taxonomicName>
. The taxonomic consequences of this insight, however, still remain to be formalized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
